The '''Chung Cheng Martial Arts Stadium''' ({{zh|c=中正技擊館|p=Zhōngzhèng Jìjīguǎn}}) is a [[stadium]] in [[Lingya District]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]. The stadium was one of the venue for the [[World Games 2009]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikimapia.org/87807/Chung-Cheng-Martial-Arts-Stadium |title=Chung Cheng Martial Arts Stadium - Kaoxiung City |publisher=Wikimapia.org |date= |accessdate=2014-05-01}}</ref>

==Structure==
The stadium is separated into the Eastern and Western Zone with three halls in each of them of an area 620 m<sup>2</sup> each. The audience stage can accommodate 1,400 people each with a total capacity of 7,000 seats.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.khms.gov.tw/en/main8.htm |title=Department of Sports, Kaohsiung City |publisher=Khms.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502003117/http://www.khms.gov.tw/en/main8.htm |archive-date=2014-05-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

==Transportation==
The stadium is accessible from [[Martial Arts Stadium metro station|Martial Arts Stadium Station]] of [[Kaohsiung MRT]].

